<plot>In 1971, when 95% of all TV shows were still family-friendly, CBS trotted out this pleasant, 8-episode Sunday night summer series. "The Ice Palace" was a big-scale, as well as unique, variety show; all the regulars were stars of the Ice Capades, and they performed inside the fictitious title locale. The guest stars listed hosted one episode each. A perfect way to end a warm summer night!</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?565915</url></doc>
